A small addon for the express.static. 

I was searching for an option to ignore files from being served by the static express module. Especially unminified or untreated js && css files. 

I have made some modification to the /express/node_modules/send/index.js to ignore file with the extension ".sec.js" or "sec.css"

USAGE 

---

secfiles

Set how "secfiles" are treated when encountered. A secfiles is a file that end by dot (".sec.css") or (".sec.js")   Note this check is done on the path itself without checking if the path actually exists on the disk. 

The default value is 'ignore'.

'allow' No special treatment for secfiles.
'deny' Deny a request for a secfile and 403/next().
'ignore' Pretend like the secfile does not exist and 404/next().

---

Minified file are normaly served with the extension ".sec.min.js" or "sec.min.css".

Maybe this modification can be integrate in futur version.

